    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The ERP process is currently the best recommendation we have (IMO) for recovery proposals.  It minimizes the work required by the client developers, while providing equal opportunity to anyone willing to put in the effort (no preferential treatment to certain users).\r\n\r\nWhile I recognize that there are _some_ people who aren't in favor of any recoveries, none have been put to the test yet (meaning none have been proposed in a client update) so we don't actually know how the community feels yet.",
