    "updated_at": "2018-04-25T03:52:30Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The ERC-20 wrapper could just as easily have a bug.  In fact, I would argue that due to the complexity of authoring yet-another-governance-layer, the chances of some layer-2 solution having a bug are _higher_ than layer-1.  Thus, we don't really solve anything by doing this.\r\n\r\nAlso, for many classes of inaccessible ETH, the user could be impacted when moving ETH into/outof the token (e.g., fat finger the address, forget to set the recipient, etc.).",
